2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses ideas from convex programming and matrix completion, which are topics in information theory. 
3. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper proposes algorithms for solving the phase retrieval problem, which involves numerical methods and optimization techniques. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper mentions the use of structured illuminations, which can be related to network structures and information flow. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image reconstruction and diffracted patterns, which are relevant to multimedia applications such as image and video processing.
